---
// src/pages/words/[...slug].astro
import Layout from '@/components/astro/layout.astro';
import '@/styles/global.css';

// --- MOCK DATA for a single article page ---
// In a real app, you would fetch this data based on the `Astro.params.slug`
const article = {
  title: 'The Unseen Artist: How AI is Redefining Creative Boundaries',
  author: {
    name: 'Jane "Synth" Doe',
    avatarEmoji: 'üë©‚Äçüíª',
    bio: 'Lead researcher at the Institute for Digital Humanities, exploring the intersection of AI, art, and ethics.',
    specialty: 'AI Ethics & Art'
  },
  category: 'Deep Dives',
  publishedDate: 'June 25, 2025',
  readTime: '8 min read',
  tags: ['#AIArt', '#Creativity', '#GANs', '#Ethics'],
  heroEmoji: 'ü§ñ'
};

const relatedArticles = [
  { id: 1, title: 'The Legal Labyrinth of AI Copyright', author: 'Jane "Synth" Doe', emoji: '‚öñÔ∏è' },
  { id: 2, title: 'Can AI Truly Understand Human Emotion?', author: 'Dr. Evelyn Reed', emoji: 'ü§î' },
  { id: 3, title: 'Prompt Engineering 101: A Beginner\'s Guide', author: 'Alex Chen', emoji: 'üõ†Ô∏è' }
];
---
<Layout title={article.title} description={`A deep dive into how AI is redefining creative boundaries by ${article.author.name}.`}>
  <main class="py-12 md:py-20">
    {/* Changed max-w-4xl to max-w-7xl to allow columns to render correctly */}
    <article class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <!-- Article Header -->
      <header class="text-center mb-12">
        <div class="text-sm font-bold text-pink-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">{article.category}</div>
        <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-black tracking-tighter text-white mb-4">{article.title}</h1>
        <div class="flex justify-center items-center gap-4 text-gray-400">
          <span>{article.author.name}</span>
          <span class="w-1.5 h-1.5 bg-gray-600 rounded-full"></span>
          <span>{article.publishedDate}</span>
          <span class="w-1.5 h-1.5 bg-gray-600 rounded-full"></span>
          <span>{article.readTime}</span>
        </div>
      </header>
      
      <!-- Main Content & Sidebar -->
      <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-4 gap-x-12">
        <div class="lg:col-span-3">
          <!-- Article Body -->
          <div class="prose prose-invert prose-lg max-w-none">
            <p class="lead">
              The line between artist and algorithm is blurring. In studios and servers around the world, a new creative partner is emerging‚Äîone born of data and powered by complex neural networks. This is not science fiction; it is the new reality of art in the 21st century.
            </p>
            <p>
              For decades, artificial intelligence was a tool, a sophisticated brush or chisel in the hands of a human creator. But recent advancements in generative models like Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs) and transformers have elevated AI from a mere tool to a collaborative, and sometimes autonomous, creator. These systems can generate photorealistic faces of people who never existed, compose music that evokes deep emotion, and write prose that is indistinguishable from human literature.
            </p>

            <blockquote class="border-l-4 border-pink-500 bg-gray-900/50 p-6 rounded-r-lg">
              "We are at a historical inflection point. AI is not just changing how we create art; it's forcing us to fundamentally reconsider what art is."
              <cite>‚Äî Dr. Evelyn Reed, Cognitive Scientist</cite>
            </blockquote>

            <p>
              Consider the case of "Portrait of Edmond de Belamy," an AI-generated artwork that sold at Christie's for an astonishing $432,500. It wasn't the work of a single artist but of a Paris-based collective, Obvious, who used a GAN algorithm. The sale ignited a fierce debate: Who is the artist? The collective who wrote the code? The algorithm that generated the image? Or is it the vast dataset of historical portraits the AI learned from?
            </p>
            
            <!-- Replaced text placeholder with an actual image element -->
            <div class="my-10">
                <img 
                    src="https://placehold.co/1200x675/111827/4d5562?text=AI-Generated+Artwork" 
                    alt="AI-Generated Artwork Placeholder"
                    class="w-full h-auto rounded-xl border border-gray-700"
                />
            </div>


            <h3>The Ghost in the Machine</h3>
            <p>
              One of the most compelling frontiers is text-to-image generation, championed by models like DALL-E 3 and Midjourney. Users type a descriptive prompt‚Äî"a photorealistic astronaut riding a horse on Mars"‚Äîand the AI conjures the image in seconds. This new medium has given rise to "prompt engineering," an art form in itself. The ability to craft the perfect sequence of words to guide the AI's "imagination" is a skill that blends poetry, programming, and visual direction.
            </p>
            <p>
              However, this power comes with ethical quandaries. The datasets used to train these models are scraped from the internet, often containing copyrighted work from millions of human artists without their consent. Is AI art a form of sophisticated plagiarism? Or is it transformative, no different from a human artist learning from their influences? These legal and ethical battles are being fought in courtrooms and classrooms right now, and their outcomes will shape the future of digital creativity.
            </p>

            <p>
              Ultimately, the rise of the AI artist doesn't signal the end of human creativity. Instead, it invites us to a new kind of collaboration. It challenges us to be better curators, more imaginative directors, and more thoughtful critics. The future of art may not be about human versus machine, but about the incredible possibilities that emerge when human and machine create together.
            </p>
          </div>
          
          <!-- Tags & Applause -->
          <footer class="mt-12 pt-8 border-t border-gray-800 flex justify-between items-center">
             <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
                {article.tags.map(tag => (
                    <span class="text-xs font-medium py-1 px-3 bg-gray-800 text-gray-400 rounded-full">{tag}</span>
                ))}
             </div>
             <button class="applause-btn flex items-center gap-2">
                <span class="text-xl">üëè</span>
                <span>Clap</span>
                <span class="text-sm font-bold bg-pink-500 text-white w-6 h-6 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center">1.2k</span>
             </button>
          </footer>
        </div>

        <!-- Sticky Sidebar -->
        <aside class="lg:col-span-1 mt-16 lg:mt-0">
          <div class="lg:sticky top-24 space-y-8">
            <!-- Author Card -->
            <div class="bg-gray-900/50 border border-gray-800 rounded-lg p-6">
              <div class="flex items-center gap-4 mb-4">
                <div class="w-16 h-16 bg-gray-800 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center text-3xl border border-gray-700">
                  {article.author.avatarEmoji}
                </div>
                <div>
                  <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-white">{article.author.name}</h3>
                  <p class="text-sm text-pink-400">{article.author.specialty}</p>
                </div>
              </div>
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-400">{article.author.bio}</p>
            </div>
            
            <!-- Related Articles -->
            <div>
              <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-white mb-4">Read Next</h3>
              <div class="space-y-4">
                {relatedArticles.map(related => (
                  <a href="#" class="group flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg hover:bg-gray-900/50 transition-colors">
                    <div class="w-12 h-12 flex-shrink-0 bg-gray-800 rounded-md flex items-center justify-center text-2xl border border-gray-700">
                      {related.emoji}
                    </div>
                    <div>
                      <p class="font-semibold text-white leading-tight group-hover:text-pink-400 transition-colors">{related.title}</p>
                      <p class="text-xs text-gray-500">{related.author}</p>
                    </div>
                  </a>
                ))}
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </aside>
      </div>
    </article>

    <!-- Comments Section -->
    <section class="max-w-3xl mx-auto mt-20 px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
        <div class="border-t border-gray-800 pt-10">
            <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-6">Join the Discussion</h2>
            <form class="space-y-4">
                <div>
                    <textarea placeholder="Write your comment..." rows="4" class="w-full p-4 bg-gray-900/50 border border-gray-700 rounded-lg text-white placeholder:text-gray-500 focus:outline-none focus:ring-2 focus:ring-pink-500"></textarea>
                </div>
                <div class="flex justify-end">
                    <button type="submit" class="btn-primary">Post Comment</button>
                </div>
            </form>
            {/* Placeholder for comments */}
        </div>
    </section>

  </main>
</Layout>

<style is:global>
  .prose {
    color: #d1d5db; /* text-gray-300 */
  }
  .prose h3 {
    @apply text-2xl font-bold text-white mb-4 mt-8;
  }
  .prose p.lead {
    @apply text-xl text-gray-300;
  }
  .prose a {
    @apply text-pink-400 hover:underline;
  }
  .prose blockquote {
    font-style: italic;
    color: #e5e7eb; /* text-gray-200 */
  }
  .prose blockquote cite {
    display: block;
    text-align: right;
    margin-top: 0.5rem;
    font-style: normal;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: #9ca3af; /* text-gray-400 */
  }
</style>
